contents.desc: This video needs a backstory. Let‚Äôs start at the beginning. We‚Äôve always dreamed of having a space where we could workout together as a family, and so the plan to create a ‚Äúgarage gym‚Äù started about 3 years ago. Over the past 3 years I have diligently collected everything you see in this video for way under actual cost, if not free in a lot of cases. Like all the blue and black mats you saw I got for FREE. My local gym had them piled up outside and they were going to throw them out because they got new ones, so I scooped them up, sanitized them and they were good as used. Then the dumbbell set I got for $100 from an estate sale last year. I built the ball pit from scratch. That‚Äôs our old tv from our first house 8 years ago. I got the mirrors discounted because they were returns due to chips in the corners. And the list goes on. So with all that said, if you dream of having a garage gym, just start looking for good deals, and over time, you may too collect an entire home gym for a fraction of the cost. Now we have a place where while the adults workout, the kids get to be kids and have a blast! #DIY #garagegym
